e license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view bennett s lebow  wikipedia bennett s lebow from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search bennett s lebow born  age – residence philadelphia pennsylvania nationality united states education bs drexel university occupation businessman known for chairman of the board of vector group spouses jacqueline finkelstein lebow children two daughters parents suara and martin lebow bennett s lebow is an american businessman and philanthropist he is the current chairman of the board of vector group nyse vgr contents  education and career  cigarettes and litigation  notable acquisitions  philanthropy and political activity  criticism  personal life  references  additional reading  external links education and careeredit lebow was born to a jewish family the son of suara and martin lebow his father was a life insurance salesman and his mother a teacher he graduated from west philadelphia high school and in  earned a degree in electrical engineering from drexel university lebow then went on to graduate school at princeton university before completing his degree lebow left princeton and joined the army where he installed early data systems at the pentagon lebows first foray into business occurred in the s when he started a computer company to continue his pentagon project lebow eventually sold the business in  for a profit and became a fulltime investor in  he founded the investment holding company brooke group ltd lebow went on to purchase many companies including western union information displays mai basic four liggett group brighams ice cream and the trading card company skybox international which he sold to marvel in  brooke group ltd was renamed vector group ltd cigarettes and litigationedit in  he purchased the th largest cigarette manufacturer in the united states the liggett group for  million in  lebow stated under sworn testimony that since cigarettes are a legal product and people choose to use them whether or not that they cause cancer is irrelevant in  while under his leadership liggett group broke ranks with the rest of the us tobacco industry including philip morris brown and williamson rjr nabisco loews and lorillard when he announced that liggett would settle the medicaid tobacco suits brought by forty state attorneys general liggett had previously been accused of being illegally influenced by philip morris which allegedly paid some of liggetts legal bills in order to buy its cooperation in antitobacco lawsuits lebow stated that the reason for the settlement was to obtain immunity for liggett from future liabilities and to prevent a future bankruptcy the settlement entailed that liggett agree to pay  million in damages publicly announce that smoking is addictive and causes cancer turn over longsecret tobacco industry documents disclose ingredients in its cigarettes and testify against the industry liggett was the first cigarette company to voluntarily put the label nicotine is addictive on their product lebows actions were pivotal to the government in their signing of the master settlement agreement in addition to this lebow was honored with a proclamation by florida governor lawton chiles for his invaluable assistance in helping florida achieve its historic  billion settlement with the tobacco industry following this presentation lebow and mr chiles addressed a group of students who saved their toughest questions for liggett group chief bennett lebow of miami one student asked if you want to be a watchdog of the industry why not get out altogether and stop making cigarettes to which he responded that if he did others would continue lebow also developed through vector tobacco inc the nicotinefree cigarette quest cigarette which is a cigarette designed to help people quit smoking also that year lebow teamed up with corporate raider carl icahn to make a bid for rjr nabisco in response to this proposed spinoff of nabisco from rjr reynolds tobacco industry analyst ellen barabas stated that i think there are people who would support a spinoff of nabisco but not by lebow one of the prime factors was lebows dubious reputation as a manager in  his shareholders sued him claiming he had taken millions of dollars in improper loans lebow settled out of court  according to court documents liggett while under lebows leadership engaged in marketing tactics that appeal to youths such as couponing sampling and “buy one get one free” offers for its cigarettes and advertised in magazines with substantial youth readership notable acquisitionsedit in  liggett bought a majority stake in western union which had a negative net worth of  million the company then renamed new valley llc eventually filed for bankruptcy but was able to pay its bondholders in full via asset sales liggett later sold its remaining interest in western union financial services inc for  billion earning it a  million profit in may  after a  million investment he became a member of the board of directors at borders group inc and was immediately elected chairman of the board replacing mick mcguire who resigned in june  lebow became ceo of borders group inc in february  borders declared bankruptcy lebow is also chairman of the board of vector group the holding company for liggett group vector tobacco new valley llc and douglas elliman philanthropy and political activityedit lebow is a large supporter of his alma mater drexel university in  drexels college of business and administration was named the bennett s lebow college of business in his honor after a contribution of  million to the university further he endowed the bennett s lebow engineering center a stateoftheart facility that houses drexels college of engineering in november  the yearold west philadelphia native contributed  million for the construction of a new facility for the lebow college of business — the th largest gift to any us business school and the biggest ever to drexel university in  lebow was named the nations rd largest charitable donor by the chronicle of philanthropy for donating more than  million to charitable causes in  lebow made a  campaign contribution to manhattan district attorney candidate leslie crocker snyder whose law firm  kasowitz benson torres  friedman  had represented the liggett group in smoking and health litigation since  criticismedit lebow has also been scrutinized a number of times for a variety of decisions and business dealings in  lebow resigned from the danafarber cancer institute board of trustees shortly after his appointment over discussions about the propriety of associating with the owner of a company which sells products that are known to cause cancer in  brooke group shareholder frank gyetvan sued lebow on behalf of other company shareholders claiming brooke had improperly lent lebow money for luxury personal items such as a  million yacht the suit was settled the following year with lebow repaying  million to brookes other shareholders and giving up his right to receive  million in preferred dividends  in  lebow was criticized for using  million to fly a planeload of friends to a london party for the launch of his foot yacht the trip came during the time lebow controlled mai systems an irvine califbased computer network company and western union both companies filed for chapter  bankruptcy reorganization in  in  lebow completed the sale of information displays which subsequently went bankrupt the buyer sued lebow and his partners for fraud and misrepresentation in the past lebows business associations have come into question in the book red mafiya how the russian mob has invaded america the author states ukrainian mob boss vadim rabinovich attended a clintongore fund raiser at the sheraton bal harbor hotel in miami rabinovich came as a guest of bennett s lebow the chairman of brooke group ltd parent of liggett a cigarette manufacturing company lebow refused to comment according to a spokesman for lebow lebows brooke group and rabinovich developed a business center and luxury hotel in kiev personal lifeedit lebow was married to geraldine cosher whom he met while they were students he was at drexel and she attended templecitation needed they had two daughters geraldine died in  they were married for  yearscitation neededbennett lebow is currently married to jacqueline finkelsteinlebow  referencesedit  vector group limited board of directors retrieved october    a b c business week magazine lebow turns over a new leaf may    lebow who is jewish even brought in a rabbi to say a prayer for the dead deal  summit towers condo association bulletin march   a b new york times an entrepreneurs highstakes move by glenn collins march    a b c d e f g philadelphia inquirer bennett s lebow a longtime businessman with a great love for drexel his alma mater by melissa dribben november    a b c britannica online bennett s lebow retrieved october    a b new york times turnaround artist bennett s lebow collecting wall streets wallflowers by barnaby j feder september    los angeles times other news march    new york times liggett to change its focus with shift from cigarettes by anthony ramirez june    new york times on cigarettes health and lawyers by michael janofsky december    citing the following deposition q if i asked you does smoking cause lung cancer a i dont know q ok and you really dont care because youre selling a legal product a correct  bloomberg bennett lebow cigarette industry break may    tobacco company paid competitors legal bills new york times july    a b inside the tobacco deal bennet lebow profile pbs frontline  business wire liggetts bennett lebow honored by florida governor lawton chiles and attorney general robert butterworth october    su