tive officer liggett group llc and liggett vector brands llc ronald j bernstein has served as president and chief executive officer of liggett group llc since september   and of liggett vector brands llc since march  and has been a director of the company since march  from july  to december  mr bernstein served as general director and from december  to september  as chairman of liggettducat ltd the company’s former russian tobacco business sold in  prior to that time mr bernstein served in various positions with liggett commencing in  including executive vice president and chief financial officer ▲bennett s lebow chairman bennett s lebow is the chairman of the company’s board of directors and has been a director of the company since october  mr lebow currently a private investor served as the company’s chairman and chief executive officer from june  to december  and executive chairman from january  until his retirement on december   he has served as chairman of the board of signal genetics inc nasdaq sgnl since january  mr lebow served as chairman of the board of directors of borders group inc from may  until january  and from june  until january  as chief executive officer of borders group inc which filed for protection under chapter  of title  of the united states bankruptcy code in february  mr lebow was chairman of the board of new valley corporation “new valley” from january  to december  and served as its chief executive officer from november  to december  new valley corporation was a majorityowned subsidiary of the company until december  when the company acquired the remaining minority interest became engaged in the real estate business and began seeking to acquire additional operating companies and real estate properties ▲howard m lorber president and chief executive officer howard m lorber is president and chief executive officer of vector group mr lorber has been with vector group and its diversified interests since  and is actively involved in the management of all of vector’s assets in addition to his role at vector group mr lorber was president chief operating officer and a director of new valley corporation from november  until its merger with vector group in december  mr lorber was chairman of the board of hallman  lorber assoc inc consultants and actuaries of qualified pension and profit sharing plans and various of its affiliates from  until december  and has been a consultant to these entities since january  chairman of the board of directors since  and chief executive officer from november  to december  of nathan’s famous inc a chain of fast food restaurants a consultant to vector group and liggett group from january  to january  a director of united capital corp a real estate investment and diversified manufacturing company since may  a director of prime hospitality corp a company doing business in the lodging industry from may  until its acquisition by blackstone group lp in november  vice chairman of the board of ladenburg thalmann financial services since may  a member of the board of directors of morgans hotel group co from march  until november  and chairman from may  to november  and a director of clipper realty inc a real estate investment company that acquires owns manages operates and repositions multifamily residential and commercial properties in the new york metropolitan area since july  he has previously served as a director of sp acquisition holdings inc mr lorber holds a bachelor of arts degree a master of science degree in taxation and an honorary doctorate from long island university where he is also a trustee ▲jeffrey s podell private investor jeffrey s podell has been a director of the company since november  and is a private investor mr podell also serves as a director of ladenburg thalmann financial services inc mr podell was a member of the new york state bar association from  until march  ▲jean e sharpe private investor jean e sharpe has been a director of the company since may  ms s